tion the person there(a different one) didn't know anything about it. I was leaving again and she told me it would be repaired when I came back. I came back to the hotel around 11pm, still not fixed. There was a new person at reception who gave me note, saying the fuse had been tripped and that I had to go in my closet and flip it back up. So I went back to my room, fumbled in the dark and flipped the switched in the fuse box, which I didn't even know was there. (I guess no one had the time in 14 hours to do it) If you do decide to book here, there is no lift. Carrying luggage up stairs was hard. You might want to request a first floor room. I had one on the second floor, the climb up the stairs was still hard. If an alarm clock is important to you, request one for your room. Also, there are a few website that states that each room comes with a DVD. That is not the case, as i did not have one. You should request a room with one if you like. I liked the room, it was small but comfortable, but service is important to me, and I'm not sure if I will go back.	
